                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 811.001/208: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">On Board <placeName>U. S. S. “George
                                Washington</placeName>
                        </hi>,” <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-12">March 12,
                        1919</date>.<lb/>[Received 10:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For Colonel House. Shall probably reach Brest at 8:30 and shall of course take
                    dinner on the boat before going ashore. Regret late arrival but in circumstances
                    of course agree to arrangements suggested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
